South Africans will once again be honoured for their contribution towards nature conservation. JOHANNESBURG - South Africans will once again be honoured for their contribution to nature conservation. The annual Living Planet Awards are hosted by the World Wide Fund, however this year they'll be held online due to COVID-19. The focus is on the Succulent Karoo region and the work being done to preserve it. Morne du Plessis from the WWF in South Africa tells us why the focus this year is on the succulent Karoo region and the work being done to preserve it.